# Talos Kubernetes Homelab

Production-style Kubernetes cluster running Talos Linux in a home lab environment.

## Infrastructure

- 4-node Kubernetes cluster
- Talos Linux immutable OS
- Git-based configuration workflows
- Containerized workloads deployed with Kubernetes

## Monitoring

- Prometheus metrics collection
- Grafana dashboards for infrastructure visualization

## Automation

- Ansible used for infrastructure automation and deployments
- Git used for configuration management
- ArgoCD

## Networking

- VLAN segmented network
- UniFi gateway and switching
- Internal service routing and cluster networking
- Tailscale
- Pangolin
- Traefik
- Crowdsec

## Purpose

This lab environment is used to experiment with:

- Kubernetes cluster operations
- Infrastructure automation
- monitoring and observability platforms
- Git-based infrastructure workflows
- Running home automations
